```
=IFERROR(INDEX(CBtrans!I:I, MATCH(1, (CBtrans!A:A=B2)*(CBtrans!C:C=C2)*(CBtrans!E:E=J2), 0)), "NO MATCH")
```

Because LibreOffice does not support array formulas with implicit intersection, we will wrap the MATCH part in SUMPRODUCT to avoid array entry:

```
=IFERROR(INDEX(CBtrans!I:I, SUMPRODUCT((CBtrans!A:A=B2)*(CBtrans!C:C=C2)*(CBtrans!E:E=J2)*ROW(CBtrans!A:A))), "NO MATCH")
```

We will write this formula to K2 through K7, then apply the fill color #FF66CC (converted to RGB "FFFF66CC") and ensure the text case is normal (as returned by the formula). After writing, we will save the workbook to the output directory, recalculate formulas, verify the values, and finally submit the output path.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.styles import PatternFill
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter

# Paths
input_path = input_spreadsheet
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
output_path = output_dir + "1_57033_init.xlsx"

# Load workbook
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
ws = wb["Sheet4"]

# Define fill
fill = PatternFill(start_color="FF66CC", end_color="FF66CC", fill_type="solid")

# Write formula to K2:K7 (column 11)
for r in range(2, 8):
    # Build formula using SUMPRODUCT for 3‑way match (Company B, Document C, Year J)
    formula = (
        "=IFERROR(INDEX(CBtrans!I:I, "
        "SUMPRODUCT((CBtrans!A:A=B{)*(CBtrans!C:C=C{)*(CBtrans!E:E=J{})*ROW(CBtrans!A:A)), "NO MATCH")"
        .format(r, r, r)
    )
    cell = ws.cell(row=r, column=11)
    cell.value = formula
    cell.fill = fill

# Save to output location
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas
await recalculate(output_path)

# Reload with data_only to verify
wb2 = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws2 = wb2["Sheet4"]
print("Verification of K2:K7 after recalculation:")
for r in range(2, 8):
    cell = ws2.cell(row=r, column=11)
    print(f"K{r}: {cell.value}")
